On AWS EC2

Sign in to the AWS Console

Navigate to EC2

Click Launch Instance

Select an AMI (Operating System Image) like Ubuntu or Windows

Choose an instance type (CPU/RAM size)

Configure network and storage

Create or select a key pair for secure SSH/RDP access

Review and launch the instance 
Video Highlight

On Azure

Sign in to the Azure Portal

Go to Virtual Machines

Click Create VM

Choose the image (Ubuntu, Windows, etc.)

Set the size (CPU/RAM)

Provide credentials (username/password or SSH key)

Configure network settings

Review and create the VM 
Video Highlight

ðŸ”§ 5. Free Tiers & Cost Considerations

AWS has a 1-year free tier on eligible EC2 instances, which is great for practice.

Azure also offers a free trial and credits (typically around 30 days with some credits) you can use to experiment with VMs without being billed immediately.

This lets learners safely create, test, and delete machines while they learn. 
